# Chicken with soy ginger sauce

* From Tyler Florance and lots of experimenting *

* 2 big handfuls fresh cilantro leaves, finely chopped
* 1/2 jalapeno, sliced
* 1 teaspoon grated fresh ginger
* 1 garlic clove, grated
* 2 limes, juiced
* Zest of 1 lime
* 2 tablespoons soy sauce
* teaspoon of mirrin
* Sea salt and freshly ground black pepper
* 1.5 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil
* Tajin, to taste
* 2 chicken breasts
* Tajin, garlic powder, and lime zest, to taste

Coat chicken breast in tajin, garlic powder, and lime zest. Cook as you would normally. Combine all ingredients before the chicken in a bowl and spoon on top of the chicken.
Serve with rice. 

Also works with tuna, salmon, and tofu 
